<br>
Slowly people began to congrigate into my dorm room (mine having a good sized TV, rather neat, and my CPU turned on to cnn.com).  The vocalization of hatred to the middle east became apparent, even the most &quot;liberal&quot; and &quot;open minded&quot; of us spewed words of hatred towards a foe in which we had no proof did such a thing.  However unknowingly to us two members from our floor were refugee's from Pakistan, they fearing for thier lives (us not even paying attention on who they were, since we have grown accustomed to them, and therefore didn't &quot;suspect&quot; them I guess) fled into their dorm room and literally bunkered themselves in.  Hate can be a horrible thing, and soon we realized what we had done.<br>
<br>
